22/12/2002
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- On Friday (20 December), the tripartite presidency unanimously nominated Adnan Terzic, 42, for prime minister. 
If parliament approves the nomination, Terzic, who is deputy leader of the Muslim Party for Democratic Action, will begin choosing his cabinet. 
He insists his government will not be based on ideology.
In other news, consultations on forming the new government of Republika Srpska continue. 
Prime Minister-designate Dragan Mikerevic said Saturday that he expects the new cabinet to be formed by 10 January.It will likely include representatives from the nationalist Serb Democratic Party, despite criticism from the West. 
(AP, AFP, PBS BiH, Tanjug, HINA - 20/12/02)
